For this week 5 of the semester, we discussed the works of Carrie Hott.
Carrie is an artist, designer, educator, assitant professor in Graphic Design.
Working from Indiana University, Carrie mentions her interests about power stemming from childhood.
Noting that from added lens of living through two tech booms: social media & A.I., contributes to their work.
Having lved through the midwest, data centers beging sprouting everywhere.
Linking that to the underlying interest with power, origins of our power, and whales.
After the exposition, we began discussing the project "Our Shiver".
Inspired many other projects, this website is completely powered by renewable solar energy. 
This solar website, consists of a raspberry pi, battery, and other components.
Drawing inspiration specifically from low-tech magazine, another solar powered website.
With an interesting feature of showcasing how much power is left in the battery for the website.
Roots aside, this concept had non-profit organizations in mind with the low-cost and functionality in mind.
Ended up becdome a website for writers, artisits as mean of connect digital infrastructure and environmental impacts.
It even came up with a book rendition, with a UV light/rainbow motif befitting of the solar powered concept.
Although the website is currently not being used due to renovations, it was still intersting to discuss.
I learned a lot about the intersection technology, environmental concern, and childhood interest contributing to a work.
